Blue-Green Deployment with Docker and NGINX
Objectives
Design and implement a zero-downtime blue-green deployment system using Docker containers and NGINX as a traffic router
Build an automated deployment pipeline that validates container health before switching live traffic between environments
Simulate and recover from deployment failures using scripted rollback logic
Prerequisites
Comfort with Linux command-line operations including file editing, process management, and shell scripting
Conceptual understanding of HTTP proxying, container networking, and deployment strategies
Lab Environment
You will work on a dedicated AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance provided by Al Nafi. The instance has a base Ubuntu installation; you will install all required tools in Task 1.

